From 85120c78a3ce1f8c22c88c45a29f6848e8b0b617 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Raghavendran Madhavan <raghmadh@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 25 Jul 2025 12:03:21 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:PLATFORM:wifi: ath12k: Minidump support for ath12k
 driver

Adding below support for Minidump framework in ath12k driver.

- Register selected structures in minidump framework.
- Live Minidump Support at runtime.
- Minidump collection during SSR.
- View allocated structures during runtime
- Enable / Disable Minidump functionality at runtime.

Register dynamically allocated kzalloc and kmalloc in the
kernel minidump driver if CONFIG_QCA_MINIDUMP is enabled.

ath12k structure list is traversed to check which structures are
to be registered for tracking in the minidump driver.

When the registered structure is freed that structure is also
removed from the table maintained in minidump driver.

Live Minidump Usage:
echo 1 > /sys/kernel/debug/ath12k/<device>/ath_debug/minidump/collect

Ex:
echo 1 > /sys/kernel/debug/ath12k/pci-0003:01:00.0/ath_debug/minidump/collect

During SSR scenario the registered structures would be collected as part of
minidump collected.

Minidump can also be enabled during kernel panic by setting U-Boot Env variable.
setenv dump_minimal 1

To collect both Minidump and full dump.
setenv dump_minimal_and_full 1

Signed-off-by: Raghavendran Madhavan <raghmadh@qti.qualcomm.com>
